From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 21:52:12 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] Fix five bugs found by end-to-end testing the full stack
 locally
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- enhanced_main: mount the basic feeds router (/posts, /comments,
  /posts/{id}/reactions, /follow, /feed, /feed/public, /users/{id}/posts).
  It was shadowed by enhanced_routes and never registered, so none of
  those paths existed and the notification triggers were unreachable.
- exceptions: register the RFC 7807 ProblemDetail handler — routes using
  jwt_auth.get_current_user returned 500 instead of 401 on missing token.
- community/routes: GET /community/events returned a dict envelope that
  failed its List[CommunityEventRead] response model and 500'd on every
  call; return the list directly.
- feeds/service: eagerly load Comment.replies before returning from
  create/update/list — CommentRead serialization lazy-loaded the
  relationship and raised MissingGreenlet under the async session.
- auth/routes: PUT /auth/profile assigned a non-mapped user.full_name
  (silent no-op — renames never persisted); split into
  first_name/last_name.

Verified locally: 43/43 API checks and 21/21 Playwright browser checks
pass, including cross-user notification triggers and DM round-trips.

https://claude.ai/code/session_01Q1rk7BZrjN1to3WbJRAPyR
